claim: During the first month after the release of the Magic: The Gathering set Coldsnap, the average secondary market price of cards with a converted mana cost of 7 exceeded $5.
extra_info: converted mana cost of 7 refers to convertedManaCost = 7; card set Coldsnap refers to name = 'Coldsnap'; percentage = DIVIDE(SUM(convertedManaCost = 7), SUM(convertedManaCost))*100
reasoning: The database does not contain any secondary market price data. There are no price columns in any table (cards, sets, foreign_data, rulings, legalities, set_translations). While the Coldsnap set exists (code CSP, released 2006-07-21) and cards with convertedManaCost = 7 can be identified, there is no way to verify any claim about average secondary market prices from this database.
